VALUES ('e4138cd7-0494-4022-99c5-44fcdc57edb5', 'Which choice completes the text with the most logical transition?', 'The committee revising the city charter wanted a document citizens could actually read, so they pruned its dense legal clauses into plain sentences. Legal scholars warned that some pruned phrases had carried precise meanings courts had refined over decades. ______, simplifying the language risked stripping away protections that the original wording had quietly guaranteed.', NULL, '[{"id":"A","text":"Even so,","is_correct":false,"explanation":"Even so concedes despite a prior point, but the final sentence develops the scholars'' warning rather than pushing against it."},{"id":"B","text":"In other words,","is_correct":true,"explanation":"In other words restates the scholars'' warning, spelling out what the loss of refined legal phrasing entails."},{"id":"C","text":"Instead,","is_correct":false,"explanation":"Instead substitutes an alternative, but the sentence clarifies the warning rather than replacing it."},{"id":"D","text":"On the contrary,","is_correct":false,"explanation":"On the contrary contradicts a prior claim, yet the sentence reinforces and explains the scholars'' concern."}]'::jsonb, 'B', 'Step 1 — Identify the warning
Scholars warned that pruned phrases carried {{yellow:precise meanings courts had refined over decades}}.
Step 2 — Why In other words
